  <mads:fieldOfActivity>Epigrammatist</mads:fieldOfActivity>
  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Writer of epigrams of the Justinian period 
    (2nd half of the 6th cent. AD), of whose epigrams at least five from the ‘Kyklos’ of 
    Agathias are extant (disputed are Anth. Pal. 5,243f. 246, 7,601, they may only with
    difficulty be attributed to him). These are erotic (5,242. the first poem is uncommonly obscene),
     ddedicatory (6,77f.) and epideictic (9,444) epigrams that may no longer be described as carefully written...
    ." Degani, Enzo (Bologna). "Eratosthenes." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2009. Brill Online. Tufts University Library.</mads:note>
  <mads:note type="source">Smith's Dictionary of Greek and Roman Biography and Mythology, Vol 2, 1867, p. 47: "Eratosthenes
    Scholasticus, the author of four epigrams in the Greek Anthology...to which may be added, on the authority 
    of the Vatican MS, a fifth, which stands in the Anthology among those of Paul the Silentiary...."</mads:note> 
